import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='total', data=data, label='Total Casualties')
    plt.title('What is the trend of total casualties over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Total Casualties')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    data = data.set_index('date')
    data[['wounds', 'other', 'disease']].plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)

    plt.title('What is the distribution of the different types of casualties?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Wounds', 'Other', 'Disease'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the average percentages
    avg_wounds_percentage = data['wounds_percentage'].mean()
    avg_other_percentage = data['other_percentage'].mean()
    avg_disease_percentage = data['disease_percentage'].mean()

    # Create a pie chart
    labels = ['Wounds', 'Other', 'Disease']
    sizes = [avg_wounds_percentage, avg_other_percentage, avg_disease_percentage]
    colors = ['#ff9999', '#66b3ff', '#99ff99']
    
    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, colors=colors, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the percentage of wounds, other, and disease casualties?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(labels, loc="best")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    
    avg_casualties = data.groupby('date')['total'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='date', y='total', data=avg_casualties)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.axhline(avg_casualties['total'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {avg_casualties['total'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average number of casualties per day?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
